{{Infobox philosopher | region = [[Western Philosophy]] | era = [[Contemporary philosophy]] | image = | caption = Bartosz Brożek | name = Bartosz Brożek | birth_date = {{birth date|mf=yes|1977|6|17}} | birth_place = [[Kraków]], [[Poland]] | alma_mater = [[Jagiellonian University]] (M.A., 2001, Ph.D., 2003) | institutions = [[Jagiellonian University]], [[Copernicus Center for Interdisciplinary Studies]] | school_tradition = | main_interests = [[Philosophy of law]], [[Logic]], [[Cognitive science]], [[Neurolaw]], [[Philosophy of mind]], [[Philosophy of science]] | influences = [[Michał Heller]], [[Ludwig Wittgenstein]], [[Karl Popper]] </small> }}
'''Bartosz Brożek''' (born 17 June 1977) is a Polish [[philosopher]] and [[jurist]] whose main research interests are in [[philosophy of law]], [[philosophy of science]], [[logic]] and [[cognitive science]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://facultymedia.jcu.edu.s3.amazonaws.com/sneconference/files/2014/01/cv_Brozek.pdf |format=PDF |title=BARTOSZ BROŻEK : CV |website=Facultymedia.jcu.edu.s3.amazonaws.com |accessdate=2017-05-06}}</ref> He is currently professor of jurisprudence at the [[Jagiellonian University]] and vice [[Dean (education)|dean]] of the Faculty of Law and Administration, as well as a deputy-director of the [[Copernicus Center for Interdisciplinary Studies]] in [[Kraków]]. Author or co-author of 20 book monographs (including ''Methods of Legal Reasoning'' from Springer, as well as ''The Double Truth Controversy'' and ''Rule-Following'' from Copernicus Center Press) and more than 70 scientific papers.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://jagiellonian.academia.edu/BartoszBrozek |title=Bartosz Brozek &#124; Jagiellonian University - Academia.edu |website=Jagiellonian.academia.edu |date= |accessdate=2017-05-06}}</ref> He holds PhDs in both law (2003) and philosophy (2007), habilitation in law (2008) and the title of full professor (2013).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nauka-polska.pl/dhtml/raporty/ludzieNauki?rtype=opis&objectId=116238&lang=pl |title=Bazy danych - Nauka Polska |website=Nauka-polska.pl |date= |accessdate=2017-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.law.uj.edu.pl/~kfpep/joomla2/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=6&Itemid=35&lang=en |title=Staff |website=Law.uj.edu.pl |date= |accessdate=2017-05-06}}</ref>
Professor Brożek received numerous awards and prizes, including the Award of the Prime Minister of Poland for the Habilitation Dissertation, the Scholarship of the Minister of Science and Higher Education for Outstanding Young Scholars, as well as the fellowship of Alexander von Humboldt Foundation. He is also a laureate of the Foundation for Polish Science MASTER programme (2015). In 2013 he was the youngest person in Poland who held the title of professor.
