'''Graeme Nicholson''' is a Canadian philosopher and Emeritus Professor of [[philosophy]] at the [[University of Toronto]] known for his research on [[ontology]], [[hermeneutics]], and [[anarchism]].<ref>[http://www.philosophy.utoronto.ca/directory/graeme-nicholson/ Nicholson at the University of Toronto]</ref><ref>John Tietz (1995). Review of Graeme Nicholson 'Illustrations of Being: Drawing upon Heidegger and upon Metaphysics' Dialogue, 34, pp 171-173. doi:10.1017/S0012217300049404.</ref> He completed his doctrate at the University of Toronto with a thesis on Heidegger directed by [[Emil Fackenheim]].<ref>''Minerva's Aviary: Philosophy at Toronto'' (1843-2003), [[John G. Slater]], University of Toronto Press, pp393-394</ref>
